  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThe window for JSON-RPC commands does not allow scrolling. If the returned result doesn't fit in the visible window, the only way (I know of) to get the whole result is to triple-click on the window to select all text, and copy it into an external editor.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-11-15 11-43-03](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/7126627/73f8395b-18f8-4b9b-a8fa-e7748f8524cc)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Select Node Management in the left pane.\r\n2. Scroll down to the JSON-RPC prompt window.\r\n3. Run any command, for example: `{\"method\":\"wakuext_peers\"}`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIf the results don't fit in the window, I can scroll down.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe results are truncated and remain partially invisible.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: Current version 0.9.90, Status Go version 0.171.12\r\n- Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04.6 LTS\r\n\r\n",
